Probably tired of people complaining about her lifestyle, former Big Brother Naija housemate, Angel Agnes Smith, has cried out over men’s perceived opinions of women on Twitter. In a recent tweet garnished with a bit of anger, Angel specifically told men to stop bothering themselves about how women choose to live their lives. “As a man; you shouldn’t have an opinion on what women do with their bodies. Not IUDs, abortion, plastic surgery, choice of clothes etc, nothing. Hopefully women are given more autonomy over their bodies and more women find the courage to fight for their autonomy; especially African women.” In another news, Angel Smith, in a recent question and answer session with her fans on Twitter, confessed that she does not engage in love making. One of her fans inquired if she enjoyed making love, to which Angel declared unequivocally that she does not participate in such activities. Mrs Sikeola Idowu, right, attending to sympathizers at her late mother's residence in Surulere, Lagos By Dipo Kehinde/ Two women who were killed by a newly employed houseboy in Lagos have been described by an insider as angels who spent their lives easing people’s pains. Eighty-nine-year-old Mrs Adejoke John, who… In "Features" Abuja - Let's be truthful with ourselves, sexual scandals are not new in Christendom, they happen every day around us.   Let's get this straight, the church is no longer safe for anybody, not even the sinners seeking redemption. There is a strong possibility that they might even get hardened in… In "News" Big Brother Naija housemate, Angel Smith has become the latest brand ambassador of a fitness brand, GetFit Nigeria. This is coming days after bagging her first endorsement deal following the conclusion of the 2021 Big Brother Naija reality show. Taking to her Instagram page to announce the deal, Angel Smith… In "Entertainment"